            "text": "Optimizing Inference Performance"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "To minimize latency, preprocess images to recommended resolutions (e.g., 300 DPI) and use batch endpoints for multiple files. Monitor API usage via headers like "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "X-RateLimit-Remaining",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and implement exponential backoff for retries. Benchmark with tools like Apache JMeter to assess throughput under load."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Handling Errors and Edge Cases"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common HTTP status codes include 400 for invalid requests, 401 for authentication failures, and 429 for rate limits. Log errors with request IDs for debugging. For low-confidence results, implement fallback mechanisms such as manual review or alternative OCR models to maintain accuracy."
          }
